      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your observation about the universe's vastness is a valid philosophical perspective, but it doesn't mean your life is meaningless; it just means it lacks eternal significance. Many people find deep purpose in the temporary, like the warmth of a sunset or a shared meal, because the experience itself is real, even if it fades. If nothing matters in the end, then every choice you make to create beauty or connection is the only true impact you can have, making the effort uniquely valuable.",
      "source": "target",
